                     <note><p style="text-align: justify; line-height: normal; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: larger;">The list of the miracles are as follows:</span></p> <p style="text-align: justify; line-height: normal; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">II-1) Fols. 74ra (l.2) &#8211; 74rb (l.10): St. Cyricus and the man possessed by a demon.</span></p> <p></p> <p style="text-align: justify; line-height: normal; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">II-2) Fols. 74rb (l.11) &#8211; 74va (l.14): St. Cyricus and St. Gabriel.</span></p> <p></p> <p style="text-align: justify; line-height: normal; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">II-3) Fols. 74va (l. 15) &#8211; 75va (l.17): St. Cyricus and Qadi, the infidel man.</span></p> <p></p> <p style="text-align: justify; line-height: normal; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">II-4) Fols. 75va (l.18) &#8211; 76ra (l.24): St. Cyricus and the woman who liked the adultery.</span></p> <p></p> <p style="text-align: justify; line-height: normal; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">II-5) Fols. 76ra (l.25) &#8211; 76vb (l.24): St. Cyricus and the man who had neither clothes no food.</span></p> <p></p> <p style="text-align: justify; line-height: normal; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">II-6) Fols. 76vb (l.25) &#8211; 77va (l.1): St. Cyricus and the man who was making the good.</span></p> <p></p> <p style="text-align: justify; line-height: normal; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">II-7) Fols. 77va (l.2) &#8211; 78ra (l.11): St. Cyricus and the infidel who was a thief.</span></p> <p></p> <p style="text-align: justify; line-height: normal; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">II-8) Fols. 78ra (l.12) &#8211; 78va (l.4): St. Cyricus and the adulteress who "married </span><span lang="EN-US" style="line-height: 115%; font-size: 10pt;">&#7692;</span><span style="font-size: 10pt;">a</span><span style="font-size: 10pt;">&#740;ada.</span></p> <p></p> <p style="text-align: justify; line-height: normal; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">II-10) Fols. 79va (l.8) &#8211; 79vb (l.10): St. Cyricus and the sick man.</span></p> <p></p> <p style="text-align: justify; line-height: normal; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">II-11) Fols. 79vb (l.11) &#8211; 80ra (l.20): St. Cyricus and the infidel horseman who was adversary of another horseman.</span></p> <p></p> <p style="text-align: justify; line-height: normal; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">II-12) Fols. 80ra (l.21) &#8211; 80vb (l.5): St. Cyricus and the man who loved the love of the world.</span></p> <p></p> <p style="text-align: justify; line-height: normal; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">II-13) Fols. 80vb (l.6) &#8211; 81ra (l.20): St. Cyricus and woman who had no husband.</span></p> <p></p> <p style="text-align: justify; line-height: normal; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">II-14) Fols. 81ra (l.21) &#8211; 82ra (l.4): St. Cyricus and the adulteress with whom no one could be compared in adultery.</span></p> <p></p> <p style="text-align: justify; line-height: normal; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">II-15) Fols. 82ra (l.5) &#8211; 83va (l.5): St. Cyricus and the presbyter.</span></p> <p></p> <p style="text-align: justify; line-height: normal; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">II-16) Fols. 83va (l.5) &#8211; 83vb (l.2): St. Cyricus and the adulterer who separated</span><span style="font-size: 10pt;"> from his wife.</span></p> <p></p> <p style="text-align: justify; line-height: normal; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">II-17) Fols. 83vb (l.3) &#8211; 84rb (l.20): St. Cyricus receiving his <em>Kidan</em>, in the day of his remembrance.</span></p> <p></p> <p style="text-align: justify; line-height: normal; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">II-18) Fols. 84rb (l.21) &#8211; 84vb (l.27): </span><span style="font-size: 10pt;">St. Cyricus and King (Y&#601;mr&#601;&#7717;ann&#228; Kr&#601;stos) in the region of "Rome".</span></p> <p></p> <p style="text-align: justify; line-height: normal; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">(</span><span style="font-size: 10pt;">S. </span><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Gr</span><span style="font-size: 10pt;">&#233;baut</span><span style="font-size: 10pt;">,</span><span style="font-size: 10pt;"> &#8220;Un nouveau recueil des miracles de l&#8217;enfant Cyriaque&#8221;, Aethiopica 3, 1935, 33-36 // </span><span style="font-size: 10pt;">mss. </span><span style="font-size: 10pt;">EMML no. 4816, fol. 59v, EMML X, 324; &#201;thiopien 339, fols. 28vb-30rb, Gr&#233;bGriaule II, 4).</span></p> <p></p> <p style="text-align: justify; line-height: normal; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">II-19) Fols. 85ra (l.1) &#8211; 85va (l.5): St. Cyricus and the monk from a remote region. </span></p> <p></p> <p style="text-align: justify; line-height: normal; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">(S. </span><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Gr</span><span style="font-size: 10pt;">&#233;baut</span><span style="font-size: 10pt;">,</span><span style="font-size: 10pt;"> &#8220;Un nouveau recueil des miracles de l&#8217;enfant Cyriaque&#8221;, Aethiopica 3, 1935, 85-86, 88-89 // </span><span style="font-size: 10pt;">mss. </span><span style="font-size: 10pt;">EMML no. 4816, fol. 60v, EMML X, 324; &#201;thiopien 339, fols. 30rb-31vb, Gr&#233;bGriaule II, 4-5).</span></p> <p></p> <p style="text-align: justify; line-height: normal; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">II-20) Fols. 85va (l.6) &#8211; 85vb (l.19): St. Cyricus and the sterile couple who was supplicating&#160; to the saint for getting a baby.</span></p> <p></p> <p style="text-align: justify; line-height: normal; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">(</span><span style="font-size: 10pt;">S. </span><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Gr</span><span style="font-size: 10pt;">&#233;baut</span><span style="font-size: 10pt;">,</span><span style="font-size: 10pt;"> &#8220;Un nouveau recueil des miracles de l&#8217;enfant Cyriaque&#8221;, Aethiopica 3, 1935, 86-87, 89-90 // </span><span style="font-size: 10pt;">mss. </span><span style="font-size: 10pt;">EMML no. 4816, fol. 61v, EMML X, 324; &#201;thiopien 339, fols. 31vb-32vb, Gr&#233;bGriaule II, 5).</span></p> <p></p> <p style="text-align: justify; line-height: normal; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">II-21) Fols. 85vb (l.20) &#8211; 86rb (l.11): </span><span style="font-size: 10pt;">St. Cyricus and the monk &#704;Elyas.</span></p> <p></p> <p style="text-align: justify; line-height: normal; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">(</span><span style="font-size: 10pt;">S. </span><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Gr</span><span style="font-size: 10pt;">&#233;baut</span><span style="font-size: 10pt;">,</span><span style="font-size: 10pt;"> &#8220;Un noveau recueil des miracles de l&#8217;enfant Cyriaque&#8221;, Aethiopica 3, 1935, 87-91</span><span style="font-size: 10pt;"> // </span><span style="font-size: 10pt;">mss. EMML no. 3469, fol. 22r, </span><span style="font-size: 10pt;">EMML VIII, 283; EMML no. 4816, fol. 62v, EMML X, 324; &#201;thiopien 339, fols. 32vb-33vb, Gr&#233;bGriaule II, 5).</span></p> <p></p> <p style="text-align: justify; line-height: normal; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">II-22) Fols. 86rb (l.12) &#8211; 86va (l.16): St. Cyricus and the man with the impure spirit.</span></p> <p></p> <p style="text-align: justify; line-height: normal; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">II-23) Fols. 86va (l.17) &#8211; 87ra (l.20): St. Cyricus and the paralytic.</span></p> <p></p> <p style="text-align: justify; line-height: normal; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">II-24) Fols. 87ra (l.21) &#8211; 88ra (l.16): St. Cyricus and the Jew.</span></p> <p></p> <p style="text-align: justify; line-height: normal; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">II-25) Fols. 88ra (l.17) &#8211; 88rb (l.12): St. Cyricus and the man from Egypt.</span></p> <p></p> <p style="text-align: justify; line-height: normal; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">II-26) Fols. 88rb (l.13) &#8211; 88va (l.12): St. Cyricus and the man in a region with a building on the insland.</span></p> <p></p> <p style="text-align: justify; line-height: normal; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">II-27) Fols. 88va (l.13) &#8211; 89ra (l.10): St. Cyricus and the bishop who placed in an island of Egypt with his son.</span></p> <p></p> <p style="text-align: justify; line-height: normal; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">II-28) Fols. 89ra (l.11) &#8211; 89rb (l.11): St. Cyricus and the infidel and evil man.</span></p> <p></p> <p style="text-align: justify; line-height: normal; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">II-29) Fols. 89rb (l.12) &#8211; 89va (l.18): St. Cyricus and the pagan woman.</span></p> <p></p> <p style="text-align: justify; line-height: normal; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">II-30) Fols. 89va (l.19) &#8211; 90ra (l.15): St. Cyricus and the man who wanted to take a wife.</span></p> <p></p> <p style="text-align: justify; line-height: normal; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">II-31) Fols. 90ra (l.16) &#8211; 90rb (l.11): St. Cyricus and the bishop.</span></p> <p></p> <p style="text-align: justify; line-height: normal; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">II-32) Fols. 90rb (l. 12) &#8211; 90vb (l.6): St. Cyricus and the big ruler who became king after a lower state.</span></p> <p></p> <p style="text-align: justify; line-height: normal; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">II-33) Fols. &#160;90vb (l.7) &#8211; 90vb (l.26): St. Cyricus and the priests who wanted to restore the church of the saint.</span></p> <p></p> <p style="text-align: justify; line-height: normal; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">II-34) Fols. 91ra (l.1) &#8211; 90ra (l.16): St. Cyricus saved the house of a monk from fire.</span></p> <p></p> <p style="text-align: justify; line-height: normal; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">II-35) Fols. 91ra (l.17) &#8211; 91rb (l.12): St. Cyricus and the pagans who waged a war against Christians. </span></p> <p></p> <p style="text-align: justify; line-height: normal; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">II-36) Fols. 91rb (l.13) &#8211; 91va (l.4): St. Cyricus and the faithful who fell into the precipice.</span></p> <p></p> <p style="text-align: justify; line-height: normal; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">II-37) Fols. 91va (l.5) &#8211; 91vb (l.1): St. Cyricus and the monk who took possession of the image (picture) of the saint.</span></p> <p></p> <p style="text-align: justify; line-height: normal; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">II-38) Fols. 91vb (l.2) &#8211; 92ra (l.6): St. Cyricus and the monk ascetic.</span></p> <p></p> <p style="text-align: justify; line-height: normal; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">II-39) Fols. 92ra (l.7) &#8211; 92ra (l.27): St. Cyricus and the man with a hen.</span></p> <p></p> <p style="text-align: justify; line-height: normal; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">II-40) Fols. 92rb (l.1) - 92va (l.13): St. Cyricus and construction of a big church in his honour.</span></p> <p></p> <p style="text-align: justify; line-height: normal; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">II-41) Fols. &#160;92va (l.14) &#8211; 92vb (l.21): St. Cyricus and the paralytic who was sick from his childhood.</span></p> <p></p> <p style="text-align: justify; line-height: normal; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">II-42) Fols. 92vb (l.22) &#8211; 93ra (l.19): St. Cyricus and the man whose name was W&#228;ld&#228; Qirqos.</span></p> <p></p> <p style="text-align: justify; line-height: normal; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">II-43) Fols. 93ra (l.20) &#8211; 93rb (l.7): St. Cyricus and the thief who denied stealing.</span></p> <p></p> <p style="text-align: justify; line-height: normal; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">II-44) Fols. 93rb (l.8) &#8211; 93rb (l.25): St. Cyricus and the paralytic whose legs were dry like a stone.</span></p> <p></p> <p><span style="line-height: 115%; font-size: 10pt;">II-45) Fols. 93rb (l.26) &#8211; 94rb (l.11): St. Cyricus and the thief who stole the clothes of a woman.</span></p> <p>The miracles are not numbered.</p></note>
